The nephew of Governor Ibikunle Amosun, Mr. Yusuf Olawale, has won Ewekoro Constituency election in the Ogun State House of Assembly on the platform of the Allied Peoples Movement (APM). Olawale would be joining 25 newly elected members in the ninth assembly expected to be inaugurated in June, this year. A list of the members-elect obtained by Daily Trust in Abeokuta, yesterday, showed that the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC)  swept 15 out of 26  seats, APM clinched seven, the African Democratic Congress (ADC) won three, while one went to the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP). The Deputy Speaker of the assembly, Olakunle Oluomo, won his re-election for Ifo constituency I on the platform of APC. Amosun's nephew, 25 others win Ogun Assembly seats Ogun 2019: It is battle between APC and APM Osoba's son floors incumbent, wins Reps seat for APC in Ogun